      <header class="FAQS-header" id="FAQS">
      <h3 class="FAQS-title">Frequently Asked Questions <a href="#" class="back-to-top-button-5">Back to the Top</a></h3>
      <div class="FAQS-content">
      <h6>How do I sign up for ACEBookings.com?</h6>
      <h4>Signing up is very simple and quick. Go to the memberships and sign up area and fill in the form and click the confirm button afterwards and you will become a member just like that!</h4>
      <h6>Is ACEBookings.com available in other cities apart from London?</h6>
      <h4>At the moment, it is only available in London but we are hoping to expand to other cities in the UK in the near future. Keep an eye out!</h4>
      <h6>Can I book tennis courts as a non-member?</h6>
      <h4>Yes, you can still book tennis courts even if you are not a member but a booking fee of £1 will be added to the final price</h4>
      <h6>Are there any cancellation fees for bookings?</h6>
      <h4>If you cancel the day before, you will not be charged a cancellation fee but if you cancel on the day, a £1 cancellation fee will be charged</h4>
      <h6>Can I change or reschedule my booking?</h6>
      <h4>Yes, you can change or reschedule your bookings at anytime</h4>
      <h6>Is there a minimum or maximum booking duration?</h6>
      <h4>There is no maximum number of hours and tennis courts you can book but the minimum number of hours is 1 hour</h4>
      <h6>How do I contact customer services if I encounter issues with my booking?</h6>
      <h4>To contact customer services regarding any problems you may have, please go to the Customer Service section and all the details will be there </h4>
      <h6>Are there any discounts or promotions available for members?</h6>
      <h4>Yes, there are discounts and promotions all year round for members, so keep an eye out on the website and your emails</h4>
